[SN]TITLE[SN]
One person in hospital following Cardiff incident

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A person has been injured and taken to hospital following an incident in Cardiff.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Part of Penarth Road in Grangetown, between North Street and North Clive Street, is currently closed while South Wales Police investigate.
The incident happened at 10:30 BST on Friday.
The injured person has been taken to the city's University Hospital of Wales by ambulance.
